\par\plain {\f0\fs20\b1\i0 Which clustering algorithm to choose?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs20\b0\i0 A partitioning methods constructs }{\f0\fs20\b0\i1 k }{\f0\fs20\b0\i0  clusters.  \uc1\u8230\'85 }{\f0\fs20\b0\i1 k }{\f0\fs20\b0\i0  is given by the user. Indeed the algorithm will construct a partition with as many clusters as desired. Of course not all values of }{\f0\fs20\b0\i1 k }{\f0\fs20\b0\i0  lead to \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 natural\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  clusterings, so it is advisable to run the algorithm several times with different values of k and to select that k for which certain characteristics or graphics look best, or to retain the clustering that appears to give rise to the most meaningful interpretation.  38}
\par\plain \f0\fs20\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs20\b0\i0 The program PAM clusters objects that are measured on }{\f0\fs20\b0\i1 p }{\f0\fs20\b0\i0 interval-scaled variables, and it can also be applied when the input data is a dissimilarity matrix (set up by DAISY) 40}
\par\plain {\f0\fs20\b0\i0 To be exactl, the average distance (or average dissimilarity) of the representative object to all other objects of the same cluster is being minimized.  For this reason, such an optimal representative objects we call the }{\f0\fs20\b0\i1 medoid }{\f0\fs20\b0\i0  of the cluster, and the method of partitioning around medoids we call the }{\f0\fs20\b0\i1 k-medoid }{\f0\fs20\b0\i0  technique. 40-}}